In Jabalpur, India, a disturbing family tragedy unfolded. A 16-year-old girl, Kavya, was involved with Mukul, a man disapproved of by her father, Rajkumar Vishwakarma. Rajkumar sent Kavya to live with a relative, likely to separate her from Mukul. CCTV footage suggests Mukul entered the Vishwakarma residence and attacked Rajkumar. Sadly, their 8-year-old son, Tanishk, witnessed the attack and was also killed by Mukul. In an attempt to conceal evidence, Tanishk's body was hidden in a fridge. Although Kavya initially reported Mukul as the culprit, police investigation revealed her involvement through a voice note and CCTV footage. The motive appears to be a combination of Kavya's defiance of her father's control and her desire to be with Mukul. The temperatures range from -150 C to 425. Without your spacesuit, you’d either freeze or instantly turn into a carbon brick, depending on which side of the planet you were standing on. Without any gear, you would survive for less than 2 minutes. ✩Venus It is a real hell. The temperature on its surface is approximately 400 C. Its surface pressure is also about 90 times greater than that of Earth. A spacesuit designed for Venus would need to be constructed of titanium. Without a spacesuit, one would get squashed in seconds, if you didn’t get turned into dust. ✩Earth: Thanks to the wonderful atmosphere, food and water, and everything else that makes our home planet liveable, you can get in a good 80 or more years here.
